Nigerian singer, Skales has praised fellow artiste, Praiz for being among the few people that truly believed in him from the begining of his music career. Skales revealed that the RnB singer who is also a producer produced his first song for a token amount. He stated this during his performance at the just concluded ‘Praiz live in Unilag’ concert. He further stated that Praiz has always supported him and continues to do so even till today. Nigerian R&B sensation, Praiz held the free concert at the Staff School Hall in Unilag on Friday, March 23rd, 2018. Music lovers present were given an unforgettable experience as superstars; Praiz, Skales, Ajebutter22, IllBliss, Shaydee, BOJ and many others took the stage to perform their biggest hits. Sponsored by MTN Music plus, the concert saw students and other young fans go home with exciting gifts like mobile phones, laptops, steam irons, electric kettles and even an acoustic guitar. See Photos Below:     The post “My First Song Was Produced By Praiz For Just N4000” – Skales appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.